Day 29/30 of my SQL Challenge 💻

Today I solved **Problem 1251 – Average Selling Price** on LeetCode.

This problem focuses on calculating the average selling price of each product using two tables: *Prices* and *UnitsSold*.
It helped me practice **JOINs, date conditions, and aggregation functions** to derive meaningful business insights from data.

Key idea:
Average Selling Price = SUM(price × units) / SUM(units)

SQL Solution:

```sql
SELECT 
    p.product_id,
    ROUND(IFNULL(SUM(p.price * u.units) / SUM(u.units), 0), 2) AS average_price
FROM Prices p
LEFT JOIN UnitsSold u
ON p.product_id = u.product_id
AND u.purchase_date BETWEEN p.start_date AND p.end_date
GROUP BY p.product_id;
```

Learning highlights:
• Using LEFT JOIN to combine tables
• Applying date range conditions with BETWEEN
• Using aggregation functions like SUM
• Formatting results using ROUND

